  "text": "Hydrochlorothiazide is known to decrease the renal clearance and subsequently increase serum concentrations of UA [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In this study, co-administration of febuxostat and hydrochlorothiazide modestly decreased the renal clearance of UA (9.5% reduction), potentially due to a hydrochlorothiazide-induced increase in the net reabsorption of UA in the renal proximal tubules. This decrease in renal clearance of UA caused a slight increase in the mean sUA concentrations over 24 and 48 h post-dosing intervals (6.5% and 7.9%, respectively). These slight increases in sUA concentrations, despite being statistically significant,were not considered clinically significant.Therefore, diuretics are not expected to diminish significantly the overall urate-lowering effect of febuxostat.",
